Handicapped Badass|For a certain value of handicapped. Jake Preston is discovered to suffer from an eye dominance problem, which makes it very difficult for him to use the Apache's monocle-based targeting system, since he's left-eyed dominant and the monocle is mounted on the right side of the helmet. Little helps him overcome this by strapping a pair of panties onto Jake's head. Little's wife mentions that Little himself had the same problem at one point.|Fire Birds|1990|Film|https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/FireBirds
An Arm and a Leg|The hero loses one of his arms in a trap while attempting to get one of the Seven Pillars, and has to get it replaced with a robotic arm that also serves as the COMP upgrade of the game. The missing arm is even reflected in game as a status ailment that deals continuous damage to the hero and prevents the player from using the COMP.|Megami Tensei II|1990|VideoGame|https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MegamiTenseiII
