Mental Health Recovery Arc|At first, Dr. Forrester thinks he has just another - if unusual - patient. Aside from the supernatural/horror aspects, the movie portrays this trope with surprising, sobering realism. John Doe is sent to the emergency psych ward because the hospital doctors don't know what to do with him. And even then, he's no shape to fill out the consent forms. Dr. Forrester secretly - and illegally - admits him into the ward, because he knows John Doe would probably get left to rot in the streets otherwise. And even then, John Doe can't legally be put under involuntary hold for more than 72 hours, and Dr. Forrester resorts to hypnosis to quickly figure out what's wrong with him. There often aren't enough medical staff on hand, so sometimes patients go unsupervised, with tragic results. While John Doe eventually remembers things,  it's really the demon imitating or giving him enough clarity to be released. The scene of  his panicking father coming to pick him up after thinking John had died is exactly how these situations can play out.|The Dead Center|2019|Film|https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheDeadCenter
